<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-278-774  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 278 774.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  March 26 1990 n360 p87(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>A new era for printing. (font libraries expand) (PM Update:Special Section)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Mehling, Herman.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Microcomputer vendors are working together to create standard fonttechnology for the Apple Macintosh and microcomputers runningMS-DOS or OS/2 Presentation Manager.andP;  Microsoft will includeintelligent font-scaling technology based on Apple System 7operating system with its OS/2 Presentation Manager and Windowsprograms.andP;  IBM will support Adobe type technology in its SystemsApplication Architecture (SAA) systems.andP;  The Microsoft TrueTypefont technology is outline font technology that facilitates theaccurate display of text of any size, at low or high resolution,on any printer or screen.andP;  TrueType's open format means that allsoftware, hardware and font manufacturers will be able to supporta consistent font set for both screen and printer.andP;  Users willneed only to obtain a single font library.andP;  A similar solutionwill be available from IBM.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Microsoft Corp. (product development)Apple Computer Inc. (products).andO;Ticker:    MSFT; AAPL.andO;Product:   System 7.0 (Operating system) (usage)Truetype (Computer font) (usage).andO;Topic:     FontsProduct DevelopmentDesktop Publishing.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>